snippet.title: Meghan Markle And Prince Harry Reportedly Confirm What We Suspected All Along
snippet.description:
The most infamous interview in recent TV history is still being talked about, some six months later. Meghan Markle and Prince Harry's tell-all sit-down with TV icon Oprah Winfrey revealed that the Duke and Duchess of Sussex had allegedly dealt with racially insensitive remarks about their son's skin color from someone in the royal family. Markle also revealed the mental health issues she was going through at the time, and how the royal family encouraged her to keep those issues to herself. And now, following the reissue of the Megxit biography "Finding Freedom," Meghan Markle and Prince Harry reportedly confirm what we suspected all along.
